<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Daniel on Christian Internet Resources</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/daniel/</link><description>Recent content in Daniel on Christian Internet Resources</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><atom:link href="https://christir.org/translations/cyv/daniel/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Daniel 1</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/daniel/chapter-01/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/daniel/chapter-01/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="daniel-chapter-1">Daniel Chapter 1&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="conversational-covenant">Conversational Covenant&lt;/h3>
&lt;h3 id="daniel-taken-to-babylon">Daniel Taken to Babylon&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>In the &lt;b>third year of Jehoiakim’s reign in Judah&lt;/b>, Nebuchadnezzar, king of Babylon, laid siege to Jerusalem. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Yahveh delivered Jehoiakim to him, along with articles from God’s Temple. He took them to the temple of his god in the land of Shinar/&lt;i>Babylonia&lt;/i> and put them in the treasury. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>He ordered Ashpenaz, his chief eunuch, to bring in some of the Israelites, including members of the royal family and the nobles, &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v4" id="v4">&lt;sup class="verse-num">4&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>young men with no defects, good looking, intelligent, educated men that could serve in the king’s court. He had &lt;i>him&lt;/i> teach them the language and literature of the Babylonians, &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v5" id="v5">&lt;sup class="verse-num">5&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>and allotted them a daily ration of the royal food and the wine he drank. He assigned them three years of education; then they were to enter his personal service. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v6" id="v6">&lt;sup class="verse-num">6&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Among them were Daniel, Hananiah, Mishael, and Azariah from the tribe of Judah. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v7" id="v7">&lt;sup class="verse-num">7&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The chief eunuch renamed them: Daniel &lt;i>was&lt;/i> Belteshazzar, Hananiah &lt;i>was&lt;/i> Shadrach, Mishael &lt;i>was&lt;/i> Meshach, and Azariah &lt;i>was&lt;/i> Abed&lt;i>-&lt;/i>nego.&lt;b> &lt;/b>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Daniel 2</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/daniel/chapter-02/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/daniel/chapter-02/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="daniel-chapter-2">Daniel Chapter 2&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="nebuchadnezzars-dream">Nebuchadnezzar’s Dream&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>In the &lt;b>second year of Nebuchadnezzar’s reign&lt;/b>, haunting dreams kept him awake. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>He gave orders to call in the magicians, conjurers, sorcerers, and astrologers to tell him what he’d dreamed. When they came in, &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>he told them, &lt;i>“I had a dream, and I’m disturbed about what it means.”&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v4" id="v4">&lt;sup class="verse-num">4&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The astrologers said in Aramaic, &lt;i>“Long live the King! Tell us the dream, and we’ll tell you what it means.”&lt;/i> &lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Daniel 3</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/daniel/chapter-03/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/daniel/chapter-03/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="daniel-chapter-3">Daniel Chapter 3&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="nebuchadnezzars-golden-statue">Nebuchadnezzar’s Golden Statue&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Nebucharnezzar made a gold image 90ft tall and 18ft wide, and set it up on the Plain of Dura in the province of Babylon. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Then he sent word to gather the satraps, prefects, governors, advisors, treasurers, judges, magistrates, and rulers of the provinces to come to the dedication of the image. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>They came and stood in front of it. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v4" id="v4">&lt;sup class="verse-num">4&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The herald declared loudly, &lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Daniel 4</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/daniel/chapter-04/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/daniel/chapter-04/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="daniel-chapter-4">Daniel Chapter 4&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="nebuchadnezzar-praises-god">Nebuchadnezzar Praises God&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;a name="_Hlk124426397">&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;/a>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>King Nebuchadnezzar to the peoples, nations, and language &lt;i>groups&lt;/i> that live all over the empire: &lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%; font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“Peace and prosperity! &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family: "Times New Roman",serif'> &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>It has seemed good to me to tell about the signs and wonders the Most High God has done for me. &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.25in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>                  &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>How great his signs,&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Daniel 5</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/daniel/chapter-05/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/daniel/chapter-05/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="daniel-chapter-5">Daniel Chapter 5&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="the-handwriting-on-the-wall">The Handwriting on the Wall&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>King Belshazzar held a huge feast for 1,000 of his nobles and drank wine with them. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>While he was tasting the wine, he sent for the gold and silver items his predecessor Nebuchadnezzar had taken out of the Temple in Jerusalem. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The king, his nobles, wives, and concubines drank out of them, &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v4" id="v4">&lt;sup class="verse-num">4&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>and praised their idols made out of gold, silver, bronze, iron, wood, and stone.&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Daniel 6</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/daniel/chapter-06/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/daniel/chapter-06/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="daniel-chapter-6">Daniel Chapter 6&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="daniel-in-the-lions-den">Daniel in the Lions’ Den&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>King &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Darius thought it good to appoint 120 satraps to oversee the empire. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>He put three commissioners over them. (&lt;/span>&lt;span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Daniel was one of them.&lt;/span>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%; font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>) The satraps would report to them, and they would protect the king’s interests. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Daniel soon distinguished himself among the satraps and other commissioners because he had exceptional ability. The king planned to appoint him over the whole empire.
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v4" id="v4">&lt;sup class="verse-num">4&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Then the commissioners and satraps tried to find some grounds for accusing him of mismanaging government affairs, but they couldn’t find any evidence of corruption. He was dependable, and they couldn’t find him negligent. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v5" id="v5">&lt;sup class="verse-num">5&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>They said, &lt;i>“We won’t find any grounds for accusing him unless it’s in connection with the Law of his god.”&lt;/i>&lt;b>           &lt;/b>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Daniel 7</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/daniel/chapter-07/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/daniel/chapter-07/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="daniel-chapter-7">Daniel Chapter 7&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="dan-625-28">Dan 6:25-28&lt;/h3>
&lt;h3 id="daniels-vision-of-the-four-beasts">Daniel’s Vision of the Four Beasts&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Previously&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>, in the &lt;b>first year of Belshazzar, king of Babylon&lt;/b>, Daniel had a dream while he was in bed. He wrote down this summary of it: &lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“During the night I had a vision. Four winds were churning up the Mediterranean Sea, &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>and four different beasts emerged from it. &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Daniel 8</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/daniel/chapter-08/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/daniel/chapter-08/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="daniel-chapter-8">Daniel Chapter 8&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="daniels-vision-of-the-ram-and-the-goat">Daniel’s Vision of the Ram and the Goat&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>In the&lt;b> third year of Belshazzar’s regency&lt;/b>, I, Daniel, had another vision. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>I was in Susa the capital, in the province Elam beside the Ulai Canal. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>I looked up and saw a ram with two horns standing by the canal. The horns were long, one longer than the other even though the longer one had grown up last. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v4" id="v4">&lt;sup class="verse-num">4&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The ram was butting west, north, and south. No other animals could stand up to it, and nobody could rescue anyone from it. It did what it pleased and became great. &lt;b>                                                                                                                       &lt;/b>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Daniel 9</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/daniel/chapter-09/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/daniel/chapter-09/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="daniel-chapter-9">Daniel Chapter 9&lt;/h2>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" align=center style='margin-top:0in;margin-right: 0in;margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:4.5pt;text-align:center'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The
&lt;b>First Year of Darius&lt;/b> Ben-Ahasuerus,&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" align=center style='margin-top:0in;margin-right: 0in;margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:4.5pt;text-align:center'>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>a Mede by Birth, King of the Babylonians&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;h3 id="daniels-prayer-for-his-people">Daniel’s Prayer for His People&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>I, Daniel, read in the scroll that Yahveh had set 70 years for Jerusalem &lt;i>to lie &lt;/i>in ruins, as revealed to Jeremiah the prophet. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>So I turned my attention to the Lord God and looked to him in prayer with fasting, burlap, and ashes. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v4" id="v4">&lt;sup class="verse-num">4&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>I confessed,                      &lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Daniel 10</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/daniel/chapter-10/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/daniel/chapter-10/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="daniel-chapter-10">Daniel Chapter 10&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="daniels-vision-of-a-messenger">Daniel’s Vision of a Messenger&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The &lt;b>third year of Cyrus, king of Persia&lt;/b>, a message came to Daniel (&lt;/span>&lt;span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Belteshazzar&lt;/span>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>) about great warfare. He understood the vision about future events.   &lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-bottom:0in; '>&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>At that time, I, Daniel, had been in mourning for three weeks. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>I didn’t eat any tasty food or meat, drink any wine, or use any lotions that whole time. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v4" id="v4">&lt;sup class="verse-num">4&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size: 12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The &lt;b>twenty-fourth of the first&lt;/b> &lt;b>month&lt;/b>, I was on the bank of the Tigris River. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v5" id="v5">&lt;sup class="verse-num">5&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>I looked up and saw a man dressed in linen&lt;i> with&lt;/i> a &lt;i>belt &lt;/i>of pure gold from Uphaz around his waist. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v6" id="v6">&lt;sup class="verse-num">6&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>His body was like beryl, his face flashed like lightning, his eyes flamed like torches, his arms and feet shined&lt;i> &lt;/i>like polished bronze, and his voice sounded like&lt;i> &lt;/i>an enormous crowd. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v7" id="v7">&lt;sup class="verse-num">7&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>I was the only one that saw the vision, but such an overwhelming sense of dread came over the men that were with me that they ran and hid. &lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v8" id="v8">&lt;sup class="verse-num">8&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>So I was alone. My strength was gone, and my healthy appearance grew deathly pale.
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v9" id="v9">&lt;sup class="verse-num">9&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>When I heard him start to speak, I passed out facedown on the ground.&lt;b>                 &lt;/b>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Daniel 11</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/daniel/chapter-11/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/daniel/chapter-11/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="daniel-chapter-11">Daniel Chapter 11&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="kings-of-the-north-and-south">Kings of the North and South&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“Three more kings will come to power in Persia. A fourth will gain far more wealth than the others. As soon as he gains power by his wealth, he’ll stir up the &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>empire&lt;i> against Greece. &lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>A strong king will come to power &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>there &lt;i>and rule as he pleases. &lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v4" id="v4">&lt;sup class="verse-num">4&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>But not long after he ascends to power, his kingdom will break up into the four points of the compass. It won’t pass on to heirs or continue with the authority he exercised. His sovereignty will cease and pass on to others than &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>descendants&lt;i>.&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;b>&lt;span style='font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>
&lt;/span>&lt;/b>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Daniel 12</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/daniel/chapter-12/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cyv/daniel/chapter-12/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="daniel-chapter-12">Daniel Chapter 12&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="the-time-of-the-end">The Time of the End&lt;/h3>
&lt;p class="MsoListBulletCxSpMiddle" style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;'>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“At that time, Michael, the great prince that guards your people, will rise up. There’ll be a distressful time like nothing since nations began. Everyone among your people who are written in the scroll will be rescued. &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Many asleep in their graves will wake up, some to eternal life, some to disgrace and eternal contempt. &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>The wise will shine as bright as the sky, including those who lead many to goodness—like the stars forever. &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>
&lt;span class="verse verse-v4" id="v4">&lt;sup class="verse-num">4&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Close up this message, Daniel, and seal the scroll till the time of the end. People will travel everywhere and spread knowledge.”&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;b>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>                                               &lt;/span>&lt;/b>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>